               <head>Homiletics</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1006-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on homiletics and significant doctrinal formulae by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 71v): completed by <persName key="person_f7459" role="scr">Nūr al-Dīn Ḥusayn</persName> in the <placeName>Muḥammadpūr</placeName> area in <persName key="person_f7241" role="oth">Kūtlah Khvājah Ashraf</persName> adjacent to parganah <placeName>Kalānawr</placeName> (Punjab, India), Wednesday, 23 Rajab 1074/20 February 1664. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Small scribal nastaʿlīq, with Arabic quotations in red and frequently fully vocalised. 
</p>
                        <p>Folio 1 is a replacement leaf with a crude nastaʿlīq hand. 
</p>
                        <p>Frequent annotations in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Folio 71 is imperfect. </p>
                        <p>Damaged binding with boards detached and folios unbound. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragile.
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
